0-8063-2020."/><meta name="citation_reference" content="Deppner, J., &amp;amp; Cajias, M. (2022). Accounting for spatial autocorrelation in algorithm-driven hedonic models: A spatial cross-validation approach. The Journal of Real Estate Finance and Economics, 68, 235–273. https://doi.org/10.1007/s11146-022-09915-y"/><meta name="citation_reference" content="Deppner, J., von Ahlefeldt-Dehn, B., Beracha, E., &amp;amp; Schaefers, W. (2023). Boosting the accuracy of commercial real estate appraisals: An interpretable machine learning approach. The Journal of Real Estate Finance and Economics, 1–38. https://doi.org/10.1007/s11146-023-09944-1 PMID:38625136"/><meta name="citation_reference" content="Friedman, J. H. (2001). Greedy function approximation: A gradient boosting machine. Annals of Statistics, 29(5), 1189–1232. https://doi.org/10.1214/aos/1013203451"/><meta name="citation_reference" content="Gilliland, M. (ed.). (2010). The Business forecasting deal: exposing myths, eliminating bad practices, providing practical solutions. John Wiley &amp;amp; Sons., https://doi.org/10.1002/9781119199885"/><meta name="citation_reference" content="Holzinger, A., Saranti, A., Molnar, C., Biecek, P., &amp;amp; Samek, W. (2022). Explainable AI methods – A brief overview. In A. Holzinger, R. Goebel, R. Fond, T. Moon, K. R. Müller, &amp;amp; W. Samek (Eds.), xxAI – Beyond explainable AI (pp. 13–38). Springer., https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-04083-2_2"/><meta name="citation_reference" content="Hong, J., Choi, H., &amp;amp; Kim, W. S. (2020). A house price valuation based on the random forest approach: The mass appraisal of residential property in South Korea. International Journal of Strategic Property Management, 24(3), 140–152. https://doi.org/10.3846/ijspm.2020.11544"/><meta name="citation_reference" content="Hu, L., He, S., Han, Z., Xiao, H., Su, S., Weng, M., &amp;amp; Cai, Z. (2019). Monitoring housing rental prices based on social media: An integrated approach of machine-learni