stricts in 2021].\"}]\n6b:[\"$\",\"meta\",\"reference-44\",{\"name\":\"citation_reference\",\"content\":\"Valier, A. (2020). Who performs better? AVMs vs hedonic models. Journal of Property Investment \u0026amp; Finance, 38(3), 213–225. https://doi.org/10.1108/JPIF-12-2019-0157\"}]\n6c:[\"$\",\"meta\",\"reference-45\",{\"name\":\"citation_reference\",\"content\":\"Wheaton, W. C. (1977). Income and urban residence: An analysis of consumer demand for location. The American Economic Review, 67(4), 620–631. https://www.jstor.org/stable/1813394\"}]\n6d:[\"$\",\"meta\",\"reference-46\",{\"name\":\"citation_reference\",\"content\":\"Wu, Y., Wei, Y. D., \u0026amp; Li, H. (2020). Analyzing spatial heterogeneity of housing prices using large datasets. Applied Spatial Analysis and Policy, 13, 223–256. https://doi.org/10.1007/s12061-019-09301-x\"}]\n6e:[\"$\",\"meta\",\"reference-47\",{\"name\":\"citation_reference\",\"content\":\"Yoshida, T., Murakami, D., \u0026amp; Seya, H. (2024). Spatial prediction of apartment rent using regression-based and machine learningbased approaches with a large dataset. The Journal of Real Estate Finance and Economics, 69, 1–28. https://doi.org/10.1007/s11146-022-09929-6\"}]\n6f:[\"$\",\"meta\",\"reference-48\",{\"name\":\"citation_reference\",\"content\":\"Public Transport Authority in Warsaw. (2022). Informator statystyczny 2021 [Statistical guide 2021].\"}]\n70:[\"$\",\"meta\",\"reference-49\",{\"name\":\"citation_reference\",\"content\":\"Public Transport Authority in Warsaw. (2022). Informator statystyczny nr XII (333) [Statistical guide no. XII (333)].\"}]\n71:[\"$\",\"meta\",\"reference-50\",{\"name\":\"citation_reference\",\"content\":\"Zyga, J. (2019). Data selection as the basis for better value modelling. Real Estate Management and Valuation, 27(1), 25–34. https://doi.org/10.2478/remav-2019-0003\""])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"}]\n76:T4d1,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"\u003cabstract xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eData-driven machine learning algorithms triggered a fundamental change in hedonic real estate pricing. However, their adaptive nonparametric structure makes inference and out-ofsample prediction challenging. This study introduces an explainable approach to interpreting machine learning predictions, which has not been done before in the local market context. Specifically, Random Forest and Extreme Gradient Boosting models are developed for residential real estate price prediction in Warsaw in 2021 on 10,827 property transactions. Model-agnostic Explainable Artificial Intelligence (XAI) methods are then used to investigate the black box decision making. The results show the practicability of applying XAI frameworks in the real estate market context to decode the rationale behind data-driven algorithms. Information about the relationships between input variables is extracted in greater detail. Accurate, reliable and transparent real estate valuation support tools can offer substantial advantages to participants in the real estate market, including banks, insurers, pension and sovereign wealth funds, as well public authorities and private individuals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/abstract\u003e"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"72:[\"$\",\"$L75\",null,{\"product\":{\"_id\":\"6747be8b8b676d152c2058de\",\"__v\":0,\"articleData\":{\"doi\":\"10.2478/remav-2025-0003\",\"journalKey\":\"REMAV\",\"volumeNumber\":\"33\",\"issueNumber\":\"1\",\"title\":{\"en\":\"\u003carticle-title\u003eAlgorithm-Driven Hedonic Real Estate Pricing – An Explainable AI Approach\u003c/article-title\u003e\"},\"isAccessible\":true,\"licenseType\":\"OpenAccess\",\"licenseText\":{\"en\":\"This work is licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.\"},\"copyright\":{\"en\":\"© 2025 Stanislav Tarasov et al., published by Sciendo\"},\"ePubDate\":\"2024-11-27T00:00:00.000Z\",\"pPubDate\":\"2025-03-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\"receivedDate\":\"2024-05-22T00:00:00.000Z\",\"acceptedDate\":\"2024-11-21T00:00:00.000Z\",\"fPage\":\"22\",\"lPage\":\"34\",\"articleCategory\":null,\"prevArticle\":\"10.2478/remav-2025-0002\",\"nextArticle\":\"10.2478/remav-2025-0004\",\"pdfUrl\":\"https://reference-global.com/download/article/10.2478/remav-2025-0003.pdf\",\"keywords\":[\"residential real estate\",\"machine learning\",\"explainable artificial intelligence\",\"mass appraisal\",\"automated valuation models\"],\"abstractContent\":{\"en\":\"$76\"},\"articleContent\":{\"en\":\"\"},\"figuresAndTables\":\"\",\"referenceList\":[{\"refId\":\"j_remav-2025-0003_ref_001\",\"citeString\":\"Algaba, E., Fragnelli, V., \u0026amp; Sánchez-Soriano, J. (Eds.). (2019). Handbook of the Shapley value. CRC Press. \u003cext-link ext-link-type=\\\"uri\\\" xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"https://doi.org/10.1201/9781351241410\\\"\u003ehttps://doi.org/10.1201/9781351241410\u003c/ext-link\u003e\",\"doi\":null,\"mixedCitation\":\"\u003cref id=\\\"j_remav-2025-0003_ref_001\\\"\u003e\\n\u003cmixed-citation\u003eAlgaba, E., Fragnelli, V., \u0026amp; Sánchez-Soriano, J. (Eds.). (2019). Handbook of the Shapley value. CRC Press. \u003cext-link ext-link-type=\\\"uri\\\" xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"https://doi.org/10.1201/9781351241410\\\"\u003ehttps://doi.org/10.1201/9781351241410\u003c/ext-link\u003e\u003c/mixed-citation\u003e\\n\u003c/ref\u003e\"},{\"refId\":\"j_remav-2025-0003_ref_002\",\"citeString\":\"Alonso, W. (1964). \u003citalic\u003eLocation and land use: Toward a general theory of land rent\u003c/italic\u003e. Harvard University Press., \u003cext-link ext-link-type=\\\"uri\\\" xmlns:xlink=\\\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\\\" xlink:href=\\\"https://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674730854\\\"\u003ehttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674730854\u003c/ext-link\u003e\",\"doi\":null,\"mixedCitation\":\"\u003cref id=\\\"j_remav-2025-0003_ref_002\\\"\u003e\\n\u003cmixed-citation\u003eAlonso, W. 